Oct 6 (Reuters) - The following financial services industry appointments were announced on Monday. To inform us of other job changes, email moves@thomsonreuters.com.

NATIXIS GLOBAL ASSET MANAGEMENT <CNAT.PA>  The French bank appointed Alex Chang as managing director and head of its Taiwan business. [ID:nL3N0S11NE]  FTI CONSULTING INC <FCN.N>  The business advisory firm said it named Richard Baxter as a senior managing director and head of indirect taxation in its European Tax Advisory practice. [ID:nL3N0S11S7]  THE BANK OF TOKYO-MITSUBISHI UFJ (BTMU) [MTFGI.UL] <8306.T> The bank said it had promoted Masato Miyachi to chief executive officer for Europe, the Middle East and Africa (EMEA), as it seeks to boost its presence in the region. [ID:nL6N0S11A0]  FALCON PRIVATE BANK  The bank appointed Erich Pfister as global head of private banking, effective Jan. 1. [ID:nL6N0S1134]